cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about training neural machine translation models to handle language varieties, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of labeled and unlabeled parallel texts, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of shared representations for multilingual translation, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of translation quality, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
